        Official Singles Chart on 13/12/2019

        13 December 2019 - 19 December 2019

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        Here is my story of all the artists.

        One day, Ed Sheeran and Taylor Swift was on a bench talking about a collaberation they could do in 2020.

        "What should we sing about", Said Ed,

        Taylor replied, "I don't know".

        Then Liam Payne came over to the bench.
        Liam Said, "Hi guys, what are you doing.
        Ed said, "Oh nothing, just thinking of a song we could do together in the new year and decade.

        Elsewhere, Shawn Mendes was doing his Christmas shopping,
        "What is there to buy", he said to himself and when he went down the mince pies aisle, he saw Camila Cabello. Shawn went over to her and said, "Shall we write another song together?"
        Camila replied, "Yes we should".
        Back at the park, Billie Eilish was sat on the bench which was two benches away from Ed and Taylor.
        "What a cold day", she said as she got her phone out. Billie then went back to her house.

        When she got back, she took off her coat and shoes, she hanged her coat up and placed her shoes in the under the stairs cupboard. She then went on her Laptop and when her Laptop was finally loaded up, she went onto the internet and looked on the Official Charts Website. She saw that Ladbaby could the Christmas #1 for a second time.
        "Oh my god", she thought and then she went on YouTube to listen to some 80s music.
        Elsewhere, Lewis Capaldi was at home celebrating his new single, "Before You Go", being released and he really wanted it to be #1 after Christmas and he was unhappy about Ladbaby because he could be this years Christmas #1. Lewis Quickly went on Instagram Stories and slagged off Ladbaby. He was swearing about them and everything. Elsewhere, George Ezra was in Great Yarmouth walking around until he saw a newspaper. On the front of the newspaper, he heard his 2018 single, "Shotgun", being played on the radio,

        "I see that everyone still likes Shotgun", he thought to himself and he continued shopping in Great Yarmouth.

        Elsewhere, Harry Styles was at home looking at the Official Charts website and he could not wait for the new chart to be updated tomorrow, "I hope Ladbaby is not this year Christmas #1 again", and then he continued looking at the Charts.

        My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always…

        ‘Dance Monkey’ by Tones & I breaks an Official Chart record! With an 11th consecutive week at #1 on the singles chart, it’s now the longest running #1 single by a female artist ever! That said, this should also be its last week at the top, as I’d be very surprised if it avoids ACR again next week. However OCC haven't announced sales nor streaming figures for 'Dance Monkey' for this past week just yet, so I can't confirm anything at the moment!

        ‘Don’t Start Now’ by Dua Lipa is still #1 on airplay, as ‘Adore You’ by Harry Styles get the top radio debut at #3!

        ‘Dance Monkey’ also remains the most watched YouTube video across the country! It spends a ninth consecutive week at the top of the chart, where it falls 1.8% in views from last week to 4.51 million views.

        The Christmas takeover strengthens yet again, as we go from nine festive songs in last week’s chart to 15 festive songs in this week’s chart!

        I mentioned this earlier in the week, but R.I.P. to both Juice WRLD & Marie Fredriksson, who died over the past week! My condolences are with their family, friends & fans.

        HARRY STYLES - ADORE YOU (#11)
        As you would expect from a mid-December chart, the holiday songs re-entering really make new Top 40 entries a lot more sparse compared to other months, so this is the only one of the week, but I honestly don’t mind that, because I like this a lot! Harry’s always been able to embrace a throwback feel to all of his solo music, but with the slinking pulses & the disco groove gives this a lot more of a 70’s feel! Even then, Harry actually has the pipes to carry that, which seem to be mostly raw devotion to a female! I do think he goes a bit too loud on the pre-chorus which don’t allow the guitars to stand out as much as they should until the more grungier solo in the bridge, but I can’t deny that this is still so sweet & more proof that a former 1D member could actually end up attracting older listeners as well as younger ones with his new album that came out today. Overall, yeah, this really impressed me on first listen, so I’m giving this a solid 8/10!

        On the albums chart, Rod Stewart claims his 10th #1 with ‘You’re In My Heart’, although it was an extremely narrow lead, as the Top 3 were separated by just 750 copies. It’s also a chart record for him, as he becomes the oldest male solo artist to reach the top spot, at 74 years & 11 months old!

        The rest of the Top 5 is: ‘The Christmas Present’ by Robbie Williams (1-2), ‘Who’ by The Who (debuts at #3, was #1 midweek), ‘Back Together’ by Michael Ball & Alfie Boe (5-4) & ‘Divinely Uninspired To A Hellish Extent’ by Lewis Capaldi (4-5).

        Sadly, ‘Romance’ by Camila Cabello only debuted at #14, which is honestly the biggest disappointment I’ve seen in the albums this year, maybe even since I started following the charts at the start of the decade!

        Looking ahead to the all-important Christmas Chart week, these songs could enter the Top 40 for the first time: ‘I Love Sausage Rolls’ by LadBaby, ‘Merry ChrisMoyles Everyone’ by Matt Hulbert, ‘Future Nostalgia’ by Dua Lipa, up to three tracks from Stormzy’s new album, more festive releases & maybe even more.

        Finally, this might be the last time I post these long reviews due to new work commitments, although I’ll still be here every Friday or on weekend rating each new arrival to the Top 40 as usual!

        Thanks for reading everyone! I hope you all have a good weekend. :)
